\fs28 \cf2 Codebase Architecture: How It Maps\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 The codebase implements a more evolved version\'a0of the same P & X architecture. Here's the mapping:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Module 1 (P-Training) 
\f1 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  
\f2\b drl/sac_agent.py
\f0\b0 \'a0+ 
\f2\b drl/train.py
\f0\b0 \'a0+ 
\f2\b drl/offline_trainer.py
\f0\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\cf2 What the codebase does:\
A single SAC (Soft Actor-Critic) agent serves as the P-Model. It trains on per-platform campaign data using:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Algorithm: SAC with automatic entropy tuning, twin Q-networks, Gumbel-Softmax for discrete actions, and Conservative Q-Learning (CQL) for offline training\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}State space: 39-dimensional vector (
\f3 drl/state_action.py:50-179
\f0 ) containing:\cf0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Core metrics: CTR, CVR, ROAS, CPA, CPC, CPM (6 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Volume: spend velocity, impression/click/conversion volume (4 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Temporal: hour, day-of-week, day-of-month, weekend, holiday, days remaining (6 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Trends: 7-day trends for CTR, CVR, ROAS, CPA, spend (5 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Competitive: impression share, auction pressure, position (3 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}ML features: audience quality, creative fatigue, predicted CVR/LTV, propensity (5 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Context: optimization goal, platform encoding, maturity, budget utilization (4 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Absolute spend: log-normalized daily spend, total spend, daily budget (3 dims)\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Audience segments: segment count, top segment ROAS, avg frequency (3 dims)\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Action space\'a0(
\f3 drl/state_action.py:274-378
\f0 ):\cf0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Continuous\'a0(2 dims): bid adjustment [-1,1], budget adjustment [-1,1]\cf0 \
\ls2\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Discrete\'a0(2 heads \'d7 4 options): audience action (HOLD/EXPAND/REFINE/EXCLUDE), creative action (HOLD/ROTATE/PAUSE_UNDERPERFORMING/TEST_NEW)\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Training data (P-training data): Historical campaign metrics from database or CSV (
\f3 drl/offline_trainer.py:42-158
\f0 ), extracted as daily snapshots with inferred or logged actions\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Module 2 (P-Execution) 
\f1 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  
\f2\b drl/safe_agent.py
\f0\b0 \'a0+ 
\f2\b drl/hybrid_optimizer.py
\f0\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\cf2 P-Execution\'a0is implemented as a two-layer system:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	1	}SafeDRLAgent\'a0(
\f3 drl/safe_agent.py:281-528
\f0 ): Wraps the trained SACAgent with production guardrails:\cf0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Bid bounds: max +50%/-30% per action\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Budget bounds: max +30%/-30% per action\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Cooldown: min 4 hours between actions, max 6 actions/day\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Confidence threshold: 0.7 minimum, 0.85 for auto-apply\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Emergency stops: ROAS < 0.5 or CPA > 3\'d7 target triggers automatic pullback\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Automatic rollback if performance drops >15% within 24 hours\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	2	}HybridDRLLLMOptimizer\'a0(
\f3 drl/hybrid_optimizer.py:188-564
\f0 ): Hierarchical DRL
\f1 \uc0\u8594 
\f0 LLM pipeline:\cf0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}DRL Macro Layer\'a0(strategic): Budget allocation, bid strategy, audience priority\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}LLM Micro Layer\'a0(tactical): Creative generation, messaging optimization, offer personalization\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}The DRL produces a 
\f3 DRLDirective
\f0 \'a0(
\f3 drl/state_action.py:393-509
\f0 ) that constrains LLM output with messaging tone, urgency level, max discount, etc.\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Execution parameters from UI\'a0
\f1 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  correspond to 
\f3 CampaignContext
\f0 \'a0(
\f3 drl/safe_agent.py:59-78
\f0 ): current bid, current budget, ROAS, CPA, target CPA, min ROAS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Module 3 (X-Training Data) 
\f1 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  
\f2\b drl/cross_platform_optimizer.py:663-781
\f0\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\cf2 X-Training data transformation\'a0is handled by 
\f3 PlatformPerformanceTracker
\f0 :\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Aggregates per-campaign metrics into per-platform portfolio metrics\cf0 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Computes platform-level ROAS, CPA, CTR, CVR, conversion trends\cf0 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Builds 
\f3 PlatformPortfolio
\f0 \'a0objects from lists of campaign (state, context, info) tuples\cf0 \
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Historical daily metrics are tracked per organization per platform (up to 90 days)\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Module 4 (X-Training DRL) 
\f1 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  
\f2\b drl/cross_platform_optimizer.py:311-417, 423-657
\f0\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The X-Model\'a0in the codebase is not a separate neural network. Instead, it uses:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	1	}MarginalReturnEstimator\'a0(
\f3 cross_platform_optimizer.py:311-416
\f0 ): Estimates diminishing returns per platform using a log-linear response model:\cf0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Revenue(spend) \uc0\u8776  a \'d7 ln(1 + spend/b)\cf0 \
\ls5\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Marginal ROAS = dRevenue/dSpend = a / (b + spend)\cf0 \
\ls5\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Uses EMA smoothing and historical daily (spend, revenue) observations\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	2	}BudgetAllocator\'a0(
\f3 cross_platform_optimizer.py:423-657
\f0 ): Solves constrained budget allocation:\cf0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Objective: maximize composite of weighted marginal ROAS + volume (log conversions) + diversification (entropy) + momentum (trend)\cf0 \
\ls5\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Constraints: \uc0\u931  budgets = total, min 5% per platform, max 80% per platform, max 20% shift per cycle, 24h cooldown\cf0 \
\ls5\ilvl1\cf2 {\listtext	
\f1 \uc0\u9702 
\f0 	}Uses softmax over composite scores with projected gradient ascent on simplex\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	3	}Budget Recommendation for New Campaigns\'a0(
\f3 cross_platform_optimizer.py:1087-1345
\f0 ): Sweeps candidate daily budgets ($50 to $50k), builds synthetic CampaignState for each, evaluates via the DRL critic Q-function, and selects the best composite score.\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa425\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Module 5 (X-Execution) 
\f1 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  
\f2\b CrossPlatformOptimizer.optimize_portfolio()
\f0\b0 \'a0(line 821-922)\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The full pipeline\'a0runs 7 phases:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	1	}Build portfolio snapshot from all campaigns\cf0 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	2	}Check rebalance cooldown (24h default)\cf0 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	3	}Estimate marginal returns per platform\cf0 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	4	}Emergency override for platforms with ROAS < 0.5\cf0 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	5	}Solve cross-platform budget allocation\cf0 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	6	}Project portfolio ROAS impact\cf0 \
\ls6\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	7	}Adjust per-campaign budgets proportionally, then run per-campaign DRL optimization\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0
